<span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: 116%;">Classic Shell Sourceforge Reviews:</span> <br /><br />, November 27, 2010, 1:41:58 | Can't live without the up button! Classic Explorer works wonderfully for me. Please be wary of the thumb down reviews: The perpetrators of many of those idiotic reviews are of the opinion that Microsoft must be rimmed. <br /><br /><br />, November 24, 2010, 10:41:53 | Fantastic piece of software that brings back most of the goodness that Windows 7 lost in translation ! <br /><br /><br />, November 22, 2010, 11:39:50 | Best tweak ever! I am using it on a netbook with W7 Starter. I hate how new menu has scroll bars. I think the person who invented the new start menu was either mentally sick, high on drugs or really drunk. Classic Start Menu offers the best usability, somebody please tell MS to stop re-inventing the bicycle. Cheers. <br /><br /><br />, November 17, 2010, 8:58:03 | Very good work, thank you. This is not only to feel in old XP-version, the usability is much better. <br /><br /><br />, November 17, 2010, 8:46:57 | cool <br /><br /><br />, November 13, 2010, 2:10:28 | Wonderful! Deactivated Breadcrumbs! Show current path in Title Bar when Aero is activated (not only in classic view)! Loads of &quot;I want my WinXP back&quot; options! Great Work! <br /><br /><br />, November 10, 2010, 12:40:52 | It is a great tool that solves many issues in Windows Explorer. The most important two are: - It fixes the folder scrolling to the bottom of the screen after expanding it. - It adds automatic refresh of the right pane when you are navigating the folder tree with the arrow keys. <br /><br /><br />, November 08, 2010, 9:47:22 | BRILLIANT, thank you so much!!! <br /><br /><br />, November 07, 2010, 8:47:31 | OpenID Userexcellent! <br /><br /><br />, November 05, 2010, 8:39:01 | Sayat Ibraimovnice program. Very useful <br /><br /><br />, November 04, 2010, 7:25:01 | excellent, it works ; personnalising the toolbar is not easy, though <br