 мечтал об этой программе. Спасибо вам огромное. <br /><br /><br />, October 25, 2010, 6:19:43 | If i ever get round to using windows 7 i would install this straight after the os is installed. But until then Windows 7 has a long way to go before it beats windows XP. I have many great video hardware and such that xp knows but am told Windows 7 doesn't know. New hardware there is none for these new smaller motherboards that are 64 bit. Not even for pci-x it is all still pci, great for xp but for no other os. Actually i download this now, to remind me what it is called. So will get newer version if ever use vista, windows 7 or newer based on the same. <br /><br /><br />, October 23, 2010, 9:08:50 | Awesome! <br /><br /><br />, October 21, 2010, 8:44:21 | One of the best projects all around! It's even not possible to thank fully for this job done - Classic Shell makes it possible to get back to serious work, and not to fiddle endlessly through useless colorfull gadgets. Once again - many thanks guys! My greatest appreciations! G. <br /><br /><br />, October 19, 2010, 4:42:16 | Sam GleskeGreat job! I'm recommending this to all my friends. <br /><br /><br />, October 18, 2010, 6:36:43 | Molto comodo e pratico, utile per ridurre lo stress delle persone abituate ad XP a digerire le grafiche di windows 7. (capi e segretarie comprese)... <br /><br /><br />, October 16, 2010, 11:40:06 | FANTASTIC!!!!!!!!!!! <br /><br /><br />, October 13, 2010, 10:39:12 | LenA very useful project. <br /><br /><br />, October 11, 2010, 1:11:34 | very useful tool, thanks for developing, shame on Microsoft, that they made it necessery! <br /><br /><br />, October 03, 2010, 7:10:56 | When I saw &quot;Classic Shell&quot; I think in Program Manager for Vista and 7 xD <br /><br /><br />, September 30, 2010, 1:11:23 | Thank you for giving me my Start menu back. Easy to install and use it has even advandced features, all of witch are really well documented and explained. <br /><br /><br />, September 26, 2010, 6:57:29 | I didn't buy Windows 7 before I found this application. Will try to donate money when times are easier. Thank you very much for your hard work. The up-arrow is easily the best feature to get back. Always at the same spot. You don't have to analyze where to click. Only one click and you're up one-level. Simple and effective. <br /><br /><br />, September 26, 2010, 5:07:13 | You basically fixed what Microsoft screwed up. Thank you. Thank you. Thank you. <br /><br /><br />, September 25, 2010, 11:21:20 | macro codersthanks <br /><br /><br />, September 23, 2010, 12:58:06 | Awesome! Thank you! Sometimes new and &quot;better&quot; is good but most of the time it sucks! Thanks again! <br /><br /><br />, September 21, 2010, 11:29:32 | Glorious. I created an account just to add my support for this. Lightweight, clean, customizable, and everything I was looking for to restore Win 7 to usability. Thank you to everyone involved! <br /><br /><br />, September 19, 2010, 9:17:35 | cool <br /><br /><br />, September 19, 2010, 1:14:42 | This is simply brilliant! <br /><br /><br />, September 19, 2010, 6:39:07 | Excellent, much needed alternative to the cramped, tiny new start menu. <br /><br /><br />, September 19, 2010, 12:21:26 | Classic Shell was the killer application that made us roll out Windows 7 in our company. @Microsoft: please check how many companies use this tool and think again! <br /><br /><br />, September 16, 2010, 1:33:22 | LOVE IT! Thank you, thank you and thank you! <br /><br /><br />, September 14, 2010, 10:37:13 | This is soo great, I owe you a beer! <br /><br /><br />, September 13, 2010, 3:17:48 | Travis RobinsonSleek and simple; just like XP. Thanks! <br /><br /><br />, September 07, 2010, 6:36:19 | paulbAWESOME. Shame on MS for removing user control, but mega thanks to you for bringing it back. <br /><br /><br />, September 06, 2010, 11:05:44 | Great program, thanks very much for it!. I missed some funcionality in Win 7 Explorer and Start Menu. Classic shell is THE answer for it! <br /><br /><br />, September 05, 2010, 11:33:27 | Perfect... I can't really say much more. To be honest, the new setting commands are a bit more abstruse than the previous version, but are worth devoting five minutes to resolve! I keep looking to see if there are updates, but I don't know why: everything it perfect as it is! Thanks for creating this absolutely essential program! <br /><br /><br />, September 02, 2010, 11:48:20 | Thanks. Now win7 is usable. Before it was a NON professional OS suitable for gamers and mp3s only. Now I can get some work done <br /><br /><br />, September 02, 2010, 12:53:30 | good work <br />, August 31, 2010, 11:17:33 | quick and easy to see the large files that you forgot or didn't know about. <br /><br /><br />, August 27, 2010, 3:37:38 | Scott PiazzaI could throw together volumes of technopraise poetry or song, but why waste so much time? Press the &quot;Download Now!&quot; - now. This app makes me feel better every time I use my computer. Isn't it time for you to feel better too? <br /><br /><br />, August 26, 2010, 10:20:12 | Thank you for the perfect Windows Classic Shell! My &quot;Must-have-Tool-2010&quot;! I like to switch between the Classic Menu and the new Windows 7 Menu, so I can use the good features from the new, and the perfect features of the old. And the &quot;More Settings&quot; is easy to use, too. Now my Windows is individual styled, and I like it. <br /><br /><br />, August 21, 2010, 8:59:50 | Thank you so much! It works perfectly and I love it. <br /><br /><br />, August 20, 2010, 5:37:22 | OpenID Userworks wonderfully, i just wish they added the classic network activity indicator, that could make it an awesome all-in-one solution! <br /><br /><br />, August 19, 2010, 11:55:29 | Absolutely flipping brilliant! I love it! <br /><br /><br />, August 19, 2010, 6:00:09 | SUPERB <br /><br /><br />, August 18, 2010, 5:55:48 | Excellent! The most useful thing is ability to quick jump to desired program by first letter. The annoying Win 7 start typing into search box, which is very frustrating if you do not want it! <br /><br /><br />, August 15, 2010, 9:10:36 | nice work!. thanks man. <br /><br /><br />, August 15, 2010, 6:35:52 | Max PashkovI hate Windows 7 because it's uncomfortable, but now I'll try it <br /><br /><br />, August 13, 2010, 4:55:12 | great, thx <br /><br /><br />, August 13, 2010, 10:27:49 | Excellent project, pass it around for goodness sake. Cheers. <br /><br /><br />, August 10, 2010, 2:16:38 | This is awesome. Works without any crashes <br /><br /><br />, August 08, 2010, 12:49:19 | The horribly cramped menu offered in Microsoft Windows 7 makes navigating a pain. And so many features that we've gotten used to in previous versions of Windows have been removed from Windows 7 as to make it difficult to do what used to be easy. Classic Menu and Classic Shell restore the easy navigation and many features that we need -- as well as offering wonderful and long-needed enhancements. These are great tools! <br /><br /><br />, July 28, 2010, 10:21:26 | cppNickThis thing is great, I love the styles, and it runs perfectly smooth. I would definitely recommend this. I can't stand that bulky monstrosity that we (were) forced to use before =) <br /><br /><br />, July 28, 2010, 1:38:37 | RyanThis program allows one to not only change the start menu in windows 7 to look like like the classic start menu in XP and windows 2000 but you can also change all aspects/items and placement of items in said menu. The program is small in file size, easy to use, does its job well and amazingly it's free (very rarely do you get those last 2 together)! Note: Some ini files will need to be edited manually to get the full effect of this program <br /><br /><br />, July 27, 2010, 7:34:46 | This is a great, great app. Microsoft should be ashamed of themselves not to include this kind of functionality from the &quot;start&quot; (no pun intended). They should pay the developer here for massively improving the usability of Win7. <br /><br /><br />, July 27, 2010, 3:40:32 | thanks <br /><br /><br />, July 27, 2010, 1:41:32 | the best <br /><br /><br />, July 26, 2010, 1:12:27 | After installing W7 it took me some time to find a proper antidotum against the MS idiotic &quot;improval&quot; of the Start-button and Win-Eplorer. But it was worth searching --- Classic Shell is the key irreplacable SW, absolutely necessary for a rational every-day work with W7. Thank you very much, excellet work. If I could I would give you 10-thumb-ups! <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br /><br />, July 24, 2010, 7:51:06 | Thanks very, very much! Excellent add-on. <br /><br /><br />, July 24, 2010, 5:16:38 | The app that allowed me to finally move from XP to Win7. One request - I would love to have the &quot;keep taskbar on top of other windows&quot; option put into Classic Shell (which MS removed) so I can have my program windows on top of the taskbar again - autohide does not cut the mustard, esp has I have the taskbar on the left over 1/3 of the screen <br /><br /><br />, July 23, 2010, 11:56:57 | This is great, thank you! <br /><br /><br />, July 22, 2010, 1:01:11 | Thank you very much for the Classic Start Menu. It is an essential tool to creating a very useful and cool Start Menu. <br /><br /><br />, July 21, 2010, 11:39:48 | The missing puzzle. Makes Windows 7 tolerable. <br /><br /><br />, July 21, 2010, 1:04:40 | Perfect ! if more skins to choose, even more perfect... <br /><br /><br />, July 19, 2010, 4:11:42 | jim63Fantastic tool. Very many thanks for his continuing development. Jim. <br /><br /><br />, July 18, 2010, 12:14:05 | Simply can't do without. <br /><br /><br />, July 14, 2010, 3:19:31 | Beautiful! Just what I wanted! <br /><br /><br />, July 12, 2010, 12:41:22 | Leave it to 3rd parties to fix Microsofts stupidities... There is still about a dozen other things that need fixed in Win7. <br /><br /><br />, July 08, 2010, 11:55:09 | perfect! <br /><br /><br />, July 08, 2010, 12:23:45 | Suppa !!! <br /><br /><br />, July 06, 2010, 2:17:45 | wonderful project.now i start using windows 7. i use classic shell menu and royale theme for windows 7. <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://satukoro.deviantart.com/art/Royale-port-to-Win7-Aero-158227540">http://satukoro.deviantart.com/art/Roya ... -158227540</a><!-- m --> thanksssssssssssssss <br /><br /><br />, June 29, 2010, 12:42:11 | Awesome, This actually makes Vista usable! If I was a MS developer, I would likely bury my head in the sand for not offering this simple option. Thanks to the guys responsible for this! <br /><br /><br />, June 28, 2010, 7:51:39 | Works great, so much nicer than the newer craptacular interfaces. <br /><br /><br />, June 28, 2010, 7:46:39 | in a word...heaven <br /><br /><br />, June 28, 2010, 3:48:09 | Thank you so much. The program installed flawlessly and popped open my programs folder. It was like finding an old friend. Why did M'soft ever leave this functional and simple interface. Thanks for bringing it back!! My pleasure to make a small donation to your work. Keep it up. <br /><br /><br />, June 26, 2010, 4:10:01 | THANK YOU SOOOOOO MUCH to whoever did this. I will be donating with paypal. Microsoft really needs to appreciate whoever did this, as this was my biggest complaint, and main reason I did not upgrade any of my pcs to win7 until now. I just wanted my UP button back, and now it seems I have full functionality (and control) of my system back! <br /><br /><br />, June 24, 2010, 7:35:24 | Great Project Very useful <br /><br /><br />, June 21, 2010, 3:31:06 | Cannot locate where to report bugs - right clicking on LH tree directory names/icons crashes any app using this. Please fix asap Thanks! Using Win 7 v6.1.7600 <br /><br /><br />, June 16, 2010, 1:24:30 | ChewyAhhh, The Monkey on my back is dead. Nice Work! <br /><br /