esome? Well, it's *awesome*! <br /><br /><br />, May 05, 2010, 12:46:00 | BrttThis is a winner ! <br /><br /><br />, May 05, 2010, 12:32:40 | I wanted what it does, it worked first try. Thanks! <br /><br /><br />, May 04, 2010, 11:51:23 | Finally a very good option to alleviate the ununderstandable lack of size-of-files-in-current-folders and <br />remaining space on current drive. Lovely ! <br /><br /><br />, May 02, 2010, 9:36:55 | Now this is what makes Windows 7 a great OS! <br /><br /><br />, April 25, 2010, 12:35:06 | Just what I needed. <br /><br /><br />, April 24, 2010, 12:34:30 | xeonBoys, you're great!! I love Classic Sheel!! Keep up the good work! <br /><br /><br />, April 22, 2010, 3:31:14 | the snownice !!! <br /><br /><br />, April 12, 2010, 5:36:00 | Merci ! Bravo !!! <br /><br /><br />, April 10, 2010, 1:31:56 | nice tool <br /><br /><br />, April 10, 2010, 9:12:47 | Works wonderfully, both start button AND explorer. (I like Explorer better.) <br /><br /><br />, April 08, 2010, 3:28:32 | Thank you so much for Classic Shell. It finally makes Windows 7 perfect. <br /><br /><br />, April 08, 2010, 8:33:05 | This is a slick app. Very professionally done with tons of options to work with. To the person who was concerned about the sub-folder menus in the root. That is a checkbox option in the configuration window. Hope this helps <br /><br /><br />, April 07, 2010, 6:31:59 | This makes Windows 7 tolerable! Thank you. <br /><br /><br />, April 07, 2010, 1:29:50 | simple but fantastic great work <br /><br /><br />, April 07, 2010, 1:09:46 | super <br /><br /><br />, April 04, 2010, 7:53:39 | Thank you sanity at last. Fantastic! Now we all need is something to replace the repetitive strain injury caused by open file save dialogs all over the screen in different folders and inconsistent views. <br /><br /><br />, April 01, 2010, 2:44:02 | Very good <br /><br /><br />, April 01, 2010, 8:37:04 | Chris ClawsonGreat utility. This fixes most of the problems I have